Package net.royalur.model

Class PlayerState

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.royalur.model.PlayerState
  • public class PlayerState
extends java.lang.Object
    A player state represents the state of a single player at a point in the game. This includes the player's score and number of pieces left to play.

      • safeCopy

        @Nonnull
public static <S extends PlayerState> S safeCopy​(@Nonnull
                                                 S state)
        Produces a copy of the player state state, and guarantees that the copy is of the same type as state. This is used to allow custom PlayerState subclasses to be created that can be copied to be modified by rule sets.
        Type Parameters:
        S - The type of the player state that is being copied.
        Parameters:
        state - The player state to copy.
        Returns:
        A copy of the player state state.
